# python Data Types are:
# 1. Text Type: str -> "Hello World"
# 2. Numeric Types: int -> 20, float -> 20.5, complex -> 1j
# 3. Sequence Types: list -> [1, 2, 3], tuple -> (1, 2, 3), range -> range(1, 10)
# 4. Mapping Type: dict -> {"key": "value"}
# 5. Set Types: set -> {1, 2, 3}, frozenset -> frozenset({1, 2, 3})
# 6. Boolean Type: bool -> True or False
# 7. Binary Types: bytes -> b"Hello", bytearray -> bytearray(b"Hello"), memoryview -> memoryview(bytes(10))
# 8. None Type: NoneType -> None
 ----------------------------------------------------

# python Operators:
    # 1. Arithmetic Operators: +, -, *, /, %, **, //
    # 2. Assignment Operators: =, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, **=, //=
--------------------------------------------------------------

# typecasting is the process of converting the data type of a value to another data type. 
